 Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."],"variants":[{"name":"Ellenor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor  , the result of blending with   Ellen ."]},{"name":"Elenor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]},{"name":"Elinor","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Eleanor ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":9,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705190,"age":40,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Eleanor Fenes was born about 1250, in Cheshire, England, her father, Giles De Frenes, was 21 and her mother, Anne Dumont, was 21. She married Richard de Vernon. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died after 1292, in Pitchcott, Buckinghamshire, England."},"et":{"about 1250–after 1292":"umbes 1250–pärast 1292","1250–1292":"1250–1292","1255–1329":"1255–1329","1279–1314":"1279–1314","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","1259":"1259","1314":"1314","1279":"1279","after 1292":"pärast 1292","1255":"1255","1230":"1230","1250